<number id="544324C34B6DFFC0FD30F8D30080F84E" box="[686,691,1917,1931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="557" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="544324C34B6DFFC0FD23F8D300F5F84E" box="[701,710,1917,1931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="557" value="2.0">2</number>
nearly convergent apically. CuAx ratio 
<number id="544324C34B6DFFC0FB19F8C0069DF842" box="[1159,1198,1902,1927]" pageId="8" pageNumber="557" value="0.6">0.6</number>
. Squama pale yellow with 
<number id="544324C34B6DFFC0FF4EF83B02EDF86B" box="[208,222,1941,1966]" pageId="8" pageNumber="557" value="6.0">6</number>
black hairs. Halter mainly pale. 
<emphasis id="D0FFEAF64B6DFFC0FDD3F83B00F1F86B" bold="true" box="[589,706,1941,1966]" pageId="8" pageNumber="557">Abdomen</emphasis>
dark metallic green, with thick pale gray pollinosity, all sternites with bristles. Hairs on abdomen pale, bristles on abdomen black. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="7AB02A614B6DFFC0FBB0F81706B1F817" box="[1070,1154,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 17" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1343,1365]" captionTargetBox="[284,1268,205,1303]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[226,1360,175,1339]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 17. Hercostomus flavus sp. nov., male. 16. Antenna, scale bar = 0.2 mm; 17. Genitalia, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: epn = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium, ph = phallus, sur = surstylus, lat = epandrial lobe, pos = postgonite, cer = cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226275/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<number id="544324C34B6DFFC0FBFDF81406B1F817" box="[1123,1154,1978,2002]" pageId="8" pageNumber="557" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
): Epandrium longer than wide; inner epandrial lobe small, outer epandrial lobe strong, thickened at tip, with 
<number id="544324C34B6DFFC0FBC9F8700656F833" box="[1111,1125,2014,2038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="557" value="2.0">2</number>
short bristles at tip, 
<number id="544324C34B6DFFC0FACAF8700751F833" box="[1364,1378,2014,2038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="557" value="1.0">1</number>
long bristle at middle. Surstylus with 
<number id="544324C34B6CFFC1FE61FF36003EFF75" box="[511,525,152,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" value="1.0">1</number>
sharp process and 
<number id="544324C34B6CFFC1FD7EFF3600DDFF75" box="[736,750,152,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" value="1.0">1</number>
short bristle. Subepandrial process with 
<number id="544324C34B6CFFC1FB2CFF3606F3FF75" box="[1202,1216,152,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" value="2.0">2</number>
long thin processes pointed apically. Cercus mainly brown, but yellowish at base, nearly triangular, with several long digitations, with brownish hairs and long black bristles. Hypandrium with 
<number id="544324C34B6CFFC1FC82FF4E0119FF3D" box="[796,810,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558" value="1.0">1</number>
inner tooth. Phallus straight. 
<emphasis id="D0FFEAF64B6CFFC1FBEAFF7106F8FF3D" bold="true" box="[1140,1227,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="558">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
